        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 5 at 6:51PM EDT by NWS Melbourne FL</headline>
        <description>At 651 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Saint Lucie Airport, or near Indrio, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Pierce, Indrio, Fort Pierce Inlet, Queens Cove, and Fort Pierce
North.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
east central Florida.</instruction>
